EWhen%20you%20buy%20through%20our%20links%2C%20Business%20Insider%20may%20earn%20an%20affiliate%20commission.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-reviews-expertise-in-product-reviews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELearn%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222122%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Image%20of%20a%20dog%20and%20cat%20sitting%20at%20a%20dining%20table%20looking%20down%20at%20a%20serving%20of%20wet%20cat%20food.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F638e3ae054ac0f001950f909%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221061%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECat%20food%20is%20like%20fast%20food%20for%20dogs%20%E2%80%94%20dogs%20love%20it%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20very%20healthy%20for%20them.%3Cp%3Eeastonchen123%2F500px%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDogs%20require%20different%20nutrients%20than%20cats%2C%20and%20eating%20cat%20food%20regularly%20can%20make%20them%20sick.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHowever%2C%20you%20usually%20don't%20need%20to%20worry%20if%20your%20dog%20eats%20a%20few%20bites%20of%20cat%20food%20here%20and%20there.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETo%20keep%20the%20kitty%20kibble%20out%20of%20reach%2C%20try%20moving%20your%20cat's%20bowl%20or%20trying%20a%20microchip%20cat%20feeder.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20dogs%20aren't%20picky%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20food.%20They'll%20happily%20scarf%20down%20whatever%20tasty%20morsels%20they%20can%20find.%20But%20what%20if%20your%20hungry%20pup%20gobbles%20up%20everything%20in%20its%20path%2C%20including%20food%20meant%20for%20your%20other%20pets%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20necessarily%20harmful%20for%20your%20dog%20to%20sneak%20a%20bite%20from%20your%20cat's%20bowl%20here%20and%20there%20%E2%80%94%20though%20of%20course%2C%20your%20cat%20might%20not%20be%20too%20pleased%20to%20find%20their%20food%20bowl%20empty.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20feeding%20your%20dog%20cat%20kibble%20or%20canned%20wet%20food%20regularly%20won't%20meet%20their%20nutritional%20needs%20in%20the%20long%20run.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWhy%20dogs%20should%20stick%20with%20dog%20food%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKibbles%20are%20kibbles%2C%20right%3F%20Wrong.%20Cats%20and%20dogs%20have%20different%20nutritional%20needs%2C%20so%20their%20food%20isn't%20interchangeable.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCat%20food%20has%20everything%20that%20a%20dog%20needs%2C%20but%20not%20in%20the%20correct%20balance.%20These%20imbalances%20could%20lead%20to%20severe%20problems%2C%20especially%20over%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dr.%20Adam%20Currier%2C%20a%20veterinarian%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffuzzy.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFuzzy%20Pet%20Health%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20cat%20food%20typically%20has%20more%20calories%2C%20fat%2C%20and%20protein%20than%20dog%20food%2C%20Currier%20says.%20This%20is%20because%20cat%20food%20contains%20a%20higher%20meat%20content%20than%20dog%20food%2C%20and%20meat%20is%20calorically%20dense.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-15110143645oak-20%26h%3D0a831ff4ba676f28413330af17c219cce08a6637f74eac056f816d8f27429793%26postID%3D638e370f722a687d217342b7%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fpets%252Fcan-dogs-eat-cat-food%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.chewy.com%252Fhills-science-diet-adult-6-large%252Fdp%252F29999%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHill's%20Science%20Diet%20Adult%206%2B%20Large%20Breed%20Dog%20Food%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20This%20dog%20food%20contains%20353%20calories%20per%20cup%20and%20is%2018.7%25%20protein%20and%2013.7%25%20fat.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-15110143645oak-20%26h%3D6cfccc79bd4029a507b25f561f6831a7121c1a038c734f6f8bbed001f53b8262%26postID%3D638e370f722a687d217342b7%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fpets%252Fcan-dogs-eat-cat-food%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.chewy.com%252Fhills-science-diet-adult-11-indoor%252Fdp%252F160319%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHill's%20Science%20Diet%20Adult%2011%2B%20Indoor%20Chicken%20Recipe%20Cat%20Food%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThis%20cat%20food%20contains%20398%20calories%20per%20cup%20and%20is%2034.7%25%20protein%20and%2020.9%25%20fat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDogs%20need%20more%20fiber%20than%20cat%20food%20can%20provide.%20They%20also%20require%20a%20different%20blend%20of%20vitamins%20and%20minerals%20to%20avoid%20nutrient%20toxicity%20and%20deficiencies%2C%20Currier%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENote%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAs%20carnivores%2C%20cats%20have%20evolved%20to%20tolerate%20high%20levels%20of%20fat%20and%20protein.%20But%20dogs%20have%20an%20easier%20time%20consuming%20multiple%20food%20sources%20and%20processing%20plant-based%20foods%2C%20like%20grains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWill%20cat%20food%20make%20them%20sick%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20seem%20like%20your%20dog%20has%20a%20digestive%20system%20of%20steel.%20After%20all%2C%20dogs%20eat%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fcan-dogs-eat-bananas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eall%20kinds%20of%20things%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20find%20inside%20your%20house%20and%20out%20of%20it%20%E2%80%94%20poop%2C%20grass%2C%20bits%20of%20trash%2C%20fruit%2C%20veggie%20peels%2C%20shoes%2C%20and%20even%20diapers.%20You%20name%20it%2C%20and%20a%20dog%20has%20probably%20eaten%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20dog%20tummies%20are%20more%20sensitive%20than%20you%20might%20expect.%20After%20all%2C%20things%20you%20eat%20regularly%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-dogs-shouldnt-eat-2016-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eavocados%2C%20chocolate%2C%20and%20grapes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20can%20poison%20and%20even%20kill%20your%20dog.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECat%20food%20can%20also%20be%20toxic%20in%20large%20amounts.%20Cats%20can%20handle%20more%20vitamin%20D%20than%20dogs%2C%20so%20cat%20food%20may%20contain%20more%20vitamin%20D%20than%20your%20dog's%20system%20can%20safely%20process.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Fanimal-veterinary%2Fanimal-health-literacy%2Fvitamin-d-toxicity-dogs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EExcess%20vitamin%20D%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20lead%20to%20kidney%20failure%20and%20may%20even%20be%20fatal%20for%20dogs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENote%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aafco.org%2Fportals%2F0%2Fsitecontent%2Fregulatory%2Fcommittees%2Fpet-food%2Freports%2Fpet_food_report_2013_midyear-proposed_revisions_to_aafco_nutrient_profiles.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAssociation%20of%20American%20Feed%20Control%20Officials%20(AAFCO)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20commercial%20dog%20food%20should%20provide%20at%20least%200.0125%20milligrams%20(mg)%20of%20vitamin%20D%2C%20but%20no%20more%20than%200.075%20mg%20per%20kilogram%20(kg)%20per%20day.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aafco.org%2FPortals%2F0%2FSiteContent%2FRegulatory%2FCommittees%2FPet-Food%2FReports%2FPet_Food_Report_2013_Midyear-Proposed_Revisions_to_AAFCO_Nutrient_Profiles.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECat%20food%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20provide%20at%20least%200.007%20mg%20of%20vitamin%20D%2C%20but%20no%20more%20than%200.75%20mg%20per%20kg%20per%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20a%20bit%20of%20cat%20food%20once%20in%20a%20while%20probably%20won't%20send%20your%20pup%20to%20the%20emergency%20vet%20%E2%80%94%20but%20if%20your%20dog%20eats%20a%20large%20quantity%20all%20at%20once%2C%20or%20on%20a%20regular%20basis%2C%20they%20may%20develop%20serious%20complications%2C%20such%20as%20pancreatitis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPancreatitis%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.akc.org%2Fexpert-advice%2Fhealth%2Fpancreatitis-in-dogs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecan%20result%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20eating%20high%20amounts%20of%20protein%20and%20fat%2C%20can%20sometimes%20be%20fatal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.akc.org%2Fexpert-advice%2Fhealth%2Fpancreatitis-in-dogs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESigns%20of%20pancreatitis%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20dogs%20may%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EVomiting%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHunched%20back%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDiarrhea%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAppetite%20loss%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELethargy%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFever%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBloated%20or%20tender%20abdomen%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Currier%2C%20a%20steady%20diet%20of%20cat%20food%20can%20also%20cause%20a%20number%20of%20health%20problems%2C%20including%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fdog-constipation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EConstipation%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20digestive%20issues%20from%20lack%20of%20fiber.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENutrient%20toxicity%2C%20a%20type%20of%20poisoning%20that%20can%20happen%20when%20your%20pet%20gets%20too%20much%20of%20a%20certain%20vitamin%20or%20mineral.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKidney%20disease%2C%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpuppy-donates-kidney-to-mom-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekidney%20failure%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBladder%20stones%2C%20which%20can%20cause%20blood%20in%20the%20urine.%20While%20small%20stones%20may%20pass%20on%20their%20own%2C%20large%20ones%20may%20completely%20block%20urine%20flow%20and%20require%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvcacanada.com%2Fknow-your-pet%2Fbladder-stones-in-dogs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemergency%20medical%20attention%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20fine%20for%20your%20dog%20to%20sneak%20a%20nibble%20of%20cat%20food%20occasionally%2C%20but%20it's%20better%20if%20they%20get%20their%20treats%20elsewhere.%20Currier%20recommends%20treats%20that%20benefit%20your%20dog's%20dental%20health%20%E2%80%94%20in%20short%2C%20you%20may%20want%20to%20offer%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-toothpaste-dental-chews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edental%20chews%3C%2Fa%3E%20instead%20of%20leaving%20the%20cat%20bowl%20available.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20If%20you're%20in%20a%20pinch%20because%20you've%20run%20out%20of%20dog%20food%20and%20can't%20get%20to%20the%20store%2C%20opt%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-15110143645oak-20%26h%3D7720ff7aca70e91d8f648d7db6fa814bbc5c95734055b578df3a688189a85e69%26postID%3D638e370f722a687d217342b7%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fpets%252Fcan-dogs-eat-cat-food%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.rover.com%252Fblog%252Fwhat-to-feed-dog-when-out-of-dog-food-homemade-diy-hacks%252F%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplain%20boiled%20rice%20and%20boneless%20lean%20chicken%20or%20eggs%3C%2Fa%3E%20instead%20of%20cat%20food.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWhat%20kind%20of%20food%20do%20dogs%20need%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20humans%2C%20dogs%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-food%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Especific%20nutritional%20needs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20how%20do%20you%20ensure%20your%20dog's%20nutrition%20is%20up%20to%20par%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20one%20thing%2C%20a%20dog%20on%20a%20well-balanced%20diet%20should%20have%20a%20healthy%2C%20shiny%20coat%2C%20Currier%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Currier%2C%20possible%20signs%20of%20a%20nutrient%20deficiency%20may%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPoor%20skin%20health%2C%20such%20as%20skin%20crusting%20or%20a%20dull%20coat%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBrittle%20nails%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EVision%20or%20hearing%20problems%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EUncoordinated%20movements%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20dog's%20diet%20consists%20mainly%20of%20dog%20food%2C%20there's%20likely%20no%20reason%20to%20call%20your%20vet%20when%20they%20gobble%20down%20a%20bowl%20of%20cat%20food%20before%20you%20can%20put%20it%20out%20of%20reach.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20you%20notice%20a%20change%20in%20behavior%20or%20any%20of%20the%20signs%20listed%20above%2C%20consider%20making%20a%20vet%20appointment%20%E2%80%94%20just%20to%20be%20on%20the%20safe%20side.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENote%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEvery%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-food%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edog%20food%20bag%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20include%20a%20feeding%20guide%20for%20pet%20parents%20that%20includes%20recommendations%20based%20on%20your%20dog's%20target%20weight%2C%20Currier%20says.%20But%20you%20can%20always%20ask%20your%20vet%20for%20more%20specific%20guidelines%2C%20if%20you're%20unsure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20helpful%20tips%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFeed%20your%20dog%20at%20least%20twice%20a%20day%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Currier%20says%20it's%20also%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20feed%20your%20dog%20more%20than%20once%20a%20day%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvcacanada.com%2Fknow-your-pet%2Ffeeding-times-and-frequency-for-your-dog%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwice%20daily%3C%2Fa%3E%20being%20the%20most%20convenient%20schedule%20for%20most%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFeed%20puppies%20more%20frequently%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Young%20puppies%20require%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvcacanada.com%2Fknow-your-pet%2Ffeeding-times-and-frequency-for-your-dog%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20frequent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20smaller-sized%20feedings%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvcahospitals.com%2Fpress-center%2Fvca-news%2Fjessica-sewell%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJessica%20Sewell%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvcahospitals.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVCA%20Animal%20Hospitals%3C%2Fa%3E%20regional%20technician%20and%20assistant%20director.%20Your%20bag%20of%20puppy%20chow%20will%20also%20feature%20feeding%20guidelines%20you%20can%20follow.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EChange%20your%20dog's%20diet%20gradually%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt's%20important%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.akc.org%2Fexpert-advice%2Fnutrition%2Fright-way-switch-dog-foods%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20a%20gradual%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20switching%20to%20a%20new%20food.%20Your%20dog's%20system%20needs%20time%20to%20adjust%2C%20Currier%20says%2C%20so%20you'll%20want%20to%20mix%20the%20new%20food%20with%20the%20old%20food%20over%20a%20period%20of%20one%20to%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESteer%20clear%20of%20grain-free%20dog%20foods%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Fanimal-veterinary%2Foutbreaks-and-advisories%2Ffda-investigation-potential-link-between-certain-diets-and-canine-dilated-cardiomyopathy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEvidence%20suggests%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20grain-free%20diet%20may%20lead%20to%20heart%20problems%20for%20dogs%2C%20such%20as%20dilated%20cardiomyopathy%20(DCM).%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fgrain-free-dog-food%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDogs%20typically%20need%20grains%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20part%20of%20a%20balanced%20diet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EStick%20with%20a%20quality%20brand%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%26quot%3BSome%20foods%20do%20contain%20higher-quality%20ingredients%2C%20so%20I%20typically%20recommend%20starting%20off%20with%20one%20of%20the%20name-brand%20diets%20like%20Purina%20One%2C%20Royal%20Canin%2C%20or%20Hill's%2C%26quot%3B%20Currier%20says.%20However%2C%20he%20adds%20that%20you%20may%20need%20to%20experiment%20to%20find%20a%20brand%20that%20fits%20your%20pet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20any%20questions%20about%20your%20dog's%20nutritional%20needs%20or%20the%20type%20of%20food%20you%20should%20feed%20them%2C%20a%20good%20next%20step%20involves%20checking%20in%20with%20your%20vet%2C%20Sewell%20recommends.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPopular%20advice%20you%20find%20online%2C%20like%20tips%20to%20feed%20your%20dog%20a%20raw%20food%20diet%2C%20may%20not%20always%20line%20up%20with%20what%20a%20qualified%20vet%20would%20recommend.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELatest%20research%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOne%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F32554799%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2020%20observational%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20involving%20over%203%2C600%20dog%20and%20cat%20owners%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Canada%2C%20Australia%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20and%20New%20Zealand%20found%20that%20unconventional%20feeding%20practices%2C%20like%20feeding%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fraw-food-diet-for-dogs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eraw%20food%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20vegan%20diet%2C%20can%20raise%20a%20dog's%20risk%20of%20nutrient%20deficiencies%20and%20health%20conditions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EHow%20to%20keep%20your%20dog%20away%20from%20the%20cat%20food%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManaging%20a%20cat%20and%20dog%20household%20can%20be%20tricky%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20feeding%20times.%20Hungry%20dogs%20sometimes%20assume%20any%20and%20all%20food%20is%20up%20for%20grabs%2C%20including%20the%20cat's.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20tips%20for%20discouraging%20your%20dog%20from%20getting%20into%20the%20cat's%20food%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EPlace%20the%20cat%20food%20out%20of%20reach%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20If%20your%20dog%20hovers%20around%20your%20cat's%20bowl%2C%20try%20moving%20it%20somewhere%20your%20dog%20can't%20reach%2C%20like%20in%20a%20tall%20cat%20tree%2C%20inside%20a%20crate%2C%20on%20top%20of%20the%20dryer%2C%20or%20on%20a%20counter%20or%20desk.%20You%20might%20even%20try%20closing%20your%20cat%20in%20a%20room%20the%20dog%20can't%20get%20to%2C%20Sewell%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EGet%20a%20special%20feeder%20for%20your%20cat%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20A%20device%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.surepetcare.com%2Fen-ca%2Fpet-feeder%2Fmicrochip-pet-feeder%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESureFeed%20Microchip%20Pet%20Feeder%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20prevent%20your%20dog%20from%20nosing%20around%20your%20cat's%20food%2C%20since%20this%20feeder%20will%20only%20open%20when%20your%20(microchipped)%20cat%20approaches.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESwitch%20to%20meal%20feeding%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20Instead%20of%20free%20feeding%20your%20cat%2C%20consider%20switching%20to%20meal%20feeding%20%E2%80%94%20feeding%20them%20at%20a%20specific%20time%20only%20%E2%80%94%20so%20you%20can%20keep%20a%20closer%20eye%20on%20your%20dog%20while%20your%20cat%20eats%2C%20Sewell%20suggests.%20Of%20course%2C%20some%20cats%20may%20not%20approve%20of%20this%20solution%2C%20so%20you%20may%20need%20to%20try%20other%20options%20for%20a%20cat%20who%20prefers%20to%20eat%20gradually.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EInsider's%20takeaway%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20occasional%20bite%20or%20stolen%20bowl%20of%20cat%20food%20usually%20won't%20harm%20your%20dog%20over%20the%20long%20term%2C%20but%20it's%20best%20to%20avoid%20feeding%20your%20dog%20an%20exclusive%20diet%20of%20cat%20food.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20getting%20enough%20of%20the%20right%20nutrients%20%E2%80%94%20or%20too%20many%20of%20the%20wrong%20ones%20%E2%80%94%20can%20affect%20your%20dog's%20health%20over%20time%2C%20leading%20to%20conditions%20such%20as%20kidney%20disease%20or%20nutrient%20toxicity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECarefully%20following%20the%20feeding%20guidelines%20on%20your%20dog's%20food%20bag%20can%20help%20ensure%20your%20dog%20enjoys%20a%20balanced%20diet.%20And%20if%20your%20dog%20loves%20the%20taste%20of%20cat%20food%2C%20strategically%20placing%20your%20cat's%20bowl%20somewhere%20your%20dog%20can't%20reach%20can%20help%20you%20keep%20both%20your%20pet%20pals%20happy%20and%20healthy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fcan-dogs-eat-cat-food%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777212678000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F638e3ad62cd2de0018d02f2d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fcan-dogs-eat-cat-food%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Only%20dog%20food%20provides%20the%20right%20balance%20of%20nutrients%20for%20your%20pup.%20Eating%20too%20much%20cat%20food%20can%20lead%20to%20serious%20complications%2C%20like%20pancreatitis.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22stephcoelhowrites%40gmail.com%20(Steph%20Coelho%2CSorin%20McKnight)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20to%20clean%20your%20dog's%20ears%20and%20what%20you%20need%20to%20do%20it%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20buy%20through%20our%20links%2C%20Business%20Insider%20may%20earn%20an%20affiliate%20commission.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-reviews-expertise-in-product-reviews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELearn%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221884%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22GettyImages%20468196914%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ea86bc4f242ab2e8b11de6a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221413%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EM_a_y_a%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere's%20how%20to%20clean%20your%20dog's%20ears%20along%20with%20the%20tools%20you%20need%20to%20make%20it%20a%20successful%20experience.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20eardrum%20is%20very%20fragile%2C%20so%20it's%20important%20to%20exercise%20caution%20while%20cleaning%20and%20follow%20these%20steps%20precisely.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlways%20consult%20your%20veterinarian%20if%20your%20dog%20shows%20signs%20of%20an%20ear%20infection%2C%20which%20may%20include%20shaking%20their%20head%2C%20holding%20it%20to%20one%20side%2C%20odor%2C%20or%20signs%20of%20pain.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThis%20article%20was%20medically%20reviewed%20by%20Dr.%20Karie%20Johnson%2C%20veterinarian%20and%20co-founder%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22summary_bullets%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvipvetvisit.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVIP%20Vet%20Visit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20mobile%20vet%20service%20in%20the%20south%20suburbs%20of%20Chicago.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20dogs%20never%20or%20rarely%20need%20to%20have%20their%20ears%20cleaned.%20For%20other%20dogs%2C%20the%20external%20ear%20canal%20may%20accumulate%20wax%20and%20debris%2C%20so%20they%20may%20benefit%20from%20regular%20at-home%20ear%20cleaning.%20This%20could%20depend%20on%20their%20breed%20(ear%20shape%2C%20presence%20of%20hair%20in%20the%20ear%20canal)%2C%20lifestyle%20(swimming)%2C%20or%20medical%20conditions%20(allergies).%20Your%20veterinarian%20can%20advise%20you%20as%20to%20whether%20or%20not%20it's%20necessary%20for%20your%20dog.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20dachshund%20Walter%20has%20long%20hound%20ears%20and%20an%20even%20longer%20ear%20canal%20where%20debris%20accumulates%2C%20so%20I%20clean%20his%20ears%20once%20a%20week.%20Based%20on%20my%20experience%20working%20as%20a%20certified%20veterinary%20technician%20at%20a%20clinic%20and%20teaching%20clients%20how%20to%20clean%20a%20dog's%20ears%2C%20you%20don't%20need%20a%20lot%20of%20tools%20to%20do%20this%20at%20home.%20Many%20of%20the%20items%20are%20human%20grooming%20tools%2C%20including%20balls%20of%20cotton%20and%20tissues.%20Your%20veterinarian%20or%20tech%20can%20help%20you%20select%20an%20ear%20cleaner%20that%20is%20right%20for%20your%20dog.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20dog%20has%20painful%20ears%20or%20strongly%20resists%20routine%20ear%20cleanings%2C%20your%20veterinarian%20can%20also%20administer%20a%20sedative%20or%20a%20short-acting%20general%20anesthetic%20and%20do%20an%20ear%20cleaning%20at%20their%20clinic.%20With%20that%20in%20mind%2C%20many%20dogs%20are%20okay%20with%20their%20owners%20cleaning%20their%20healthy%20ears%20between%20vet%20visits.%20%26quot%3BMost%20dogs%20can%20learn%20to%20tolerate%20this%20with%20patience%20and%20treats%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr.%20Brian%20Collins%2C%20faculty%20veterinarian%20at%20Cornell%20University%20College%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20routine%20at-home%20cleanings%20can%20support%20your%20dog's%20ear%20health%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20consult%20your%20veterinarian%20if%20there%20are%20any%20signs%20of%20infection.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20notice%20your%20dog%20shaking%20her%20head%2C%20holding%20her%20head%20to%20one%20side%2C%20or%20if%20you%20notice%20an%20odd%20odor%20or%20signs%20of%20pain%2C%20have%20your%20veterinarian%20examine%20her%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Collins.%20A%20veterinarian%20will%20examine%20your%20dog's%20ears%2C%20take%20a%20sample%20of%20discharge%20for%20further%20evaluation%2C%20prescribe%20any%20necessary%20medications%2C%20and%20potentially%20do%20an%20in-office%20cleaning.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EHere's%20how%20to%20clean%20your%20dog's%20ears%20at%20home%3A%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20to%20find%20the%20right%20ear%20cleaner%20and%20wipes%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22supplies%20you%20need%20to%20clean%20your%20dog's%20ears%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ea86ad8d553f8293d690865%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EChristine%20Caplan%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20don't%20need%20a%20lot%20of%20tools%20to%20clean%20your%20dog's%20ears%20at%20home.%20Many%20of%20the%20items%20are%20human%20grooming%20tools%2C%20including%20balls%20of%20cotton%2C%20tissues%2C%20or%20baby%20wipes.%20Your%20veterinarian%20can%20help%20you%20select%20an%20ear%20cleaner%20that%20is%20right%20for%20your%20dog.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOver-the-counter%20ear%20cleaners%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20wide%20range%20of%20ear%20cleaners%20is%20available%20both%20through%20your%20veterinarian%20as%20well%20as%20online.%20Ear%20cleaners%20contain%20a%20range%20of%20ingredients%20that%20help%20to%20break%20up%20waxy%20build-up%2C%20dry%20out%20the%20ear%20canals%2C%20and%20help%20kill%20bacteria%20and%20yeast%2C%20while%20being%20designed%20to%20be%20gentle%20on%20the%20ear.%20For%20routine%20cleaning%2C%20Collins%20recommends%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-151263443005l-20%26h%3D1fc01fa6de2191a4c2dcf4b65a048103fa1528abaf3af07606b04c19307fcdca%26postID%3D61b8efdbf2a36b1ac9f49103%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fpets%252Fhow-to-clean-dogs-ears%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fprf.hn%252Fclick%252Fcamref%253A1011l4Nww%252Fdestination%253Ahttps%25253A%25252F%25252Fwww.chewy.com%25252Fvirbac-epi-otic-advanced-ear-cleaner%25252Fdp%25252F52807%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVirbac's%20Epi-Otic%20Advanced%20Ear%20Cleaner%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-151263443005l-20%26h%3D5862d601b6b24250f9559732f0016869b2b4b86414cc7cbdcb913bd0fb272cf6%26postID%3D61b8efdbf2a36b1ac9f49103%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fpets%252Fhow-to-clean-dogs-ears%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fprf.hn%252Fclick%252Fcamref%253A1011l4Nww%252Fdestination%253Ahttps%25253A%25252F%25252Fwww.chewy.com%25252Fsodium-chloride-generic-irrigation%25252Fdp%25252F204769%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaline%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Products%20such%20as%20witch%20hazel%2C%20alcohol%2C%20or%20hydrogen%20peroxide%20should%