SpiritDog%20Training%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EHairless%20breeds%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESince%20they%20don't%20have%20fur%20to%20protect%20their%20skin%2C%20hairless%20dogs%20like%20the%20Chinese%20Crested%20actually%20need%20a%20bath%20about%20once%20a%20week%2C%20according%20to%20Wigfall.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EWrinkly%20breeds%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EPugs%2C%20bulldogs%2C%20and%20shar%20peis%20may%20need%20to%20have%20their%20skin%20folds%20cleaned%20more%20regularly%20to%20avoid%20bacteria%20and%20dirt%20build-up%2C%20which%20can%20cause%20infections%2C%20Wigfall%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorking%20dogs%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAnother%20factor%20to%20consider%20is%20your%20dog's%20lifestyle%20and%20activity%20level.%20For%20example%2C%20Wigfall%20says%20a%20working%20collie%20on%20a%20sheep%20farm%20exposed%20to%20more%20dirt%20and%20livestock%20feces%20will%20require%20more%20frequent%20bathing%20than%20a%20Maltese%20who%20spends%20most%20of%20its%20time%20indoors.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EDogs%20with%20health%20conditions%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDogs%20with%20certain%20health%20conditions%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fhow-to-stop-dandruff%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edandruff%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fhow-to-treat-a-yeast-infection%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyeast%20infections%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20may%20need%20more%20frequent%20baths%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-medicated-shampoo-for-dogs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emedicated%20shampoos%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20flare-ups%2C%20Simon%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENote%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIf%20you%20or%20someone%20else%20in%20your%20household%20has%20a%20sensitivity%20or%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhypoallergenic-dogs-2019-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eallergy%20to%20your%20dog's%20dander%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20may%20need%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facaai.org%2Fallergies%2Fallergic-conditions%2Fpet-allergies%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewash%20your%20pet%20more%20often%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20goes%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Fseasonal-allergies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eallergies%20to%20dust%20and%20pollen%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20too%2C%20since%20both%20of%20these%20can%20get%20stuck%20in%20your%20dog's%20fur%20or%20hair.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EHow%20often%20is%20too%20often%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20probably%20don't%20need%20to%20bathe%20your%20dog%20as%20often%20as%20you%20think%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aspca.org%2Fpet-care%2Fdog-care%2Fdog-grooming-tips%5C%22%3Eonce%20every%20three%20months%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20good%20goal%20to%20aim%20for%2C%20unless%20they%20have%20a%20skin%20condition%20or%20get%20very%20dirty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20bathe%20your%20dog%20too%20often%2C%20you%20strip%20the%20natural%20protective%20oils%20on%20their%20skin%20and%20coat%2C%20according%20to%20Wigfall.%20This%20can%20lead%20to%20dry%2C%20irritated%20skin%20and%20a%20dull%20coat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Wigfall%20recommends%20rinsing%20away%20dirt%20and%20bacteria%20with%20plain%20water%20to%20keep%20your%20dog's%20coat%20clean%20and%20healthy%20in%20between%20baths%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20advises%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-brush%5C%22%3Ebrushing%20dogs%20with%20longer%20hair%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20least%20three%20times%20per%20week%20to%20help%20dislodge%20any%20dirt%20or%20debris.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBrushing%20your%20dog%20regularly%20can%20also%20help%20reduce%20dander%20in%20the%20house%20%E2%80%94%20just%20make%20sure%20to%20take%20the%20brushing%20session%20outside.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EWhat%20if%20you%20don't%20bathe%20them%20frequently%20enough%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20obvious%20consequences%20of%20not%20bathing%20your%20dog%20regularly%20include%20an%20unpleasant%20odor%20and%20some%20dirty%20paw%20prints%20on%20your%20carpet.%20But%20it%20can%20also%20cause%20more%20severe%20health%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeaving%20dirt%20and%20debris%20in%20areas%20that%20may%20cause%20rubbing%20%E2%80%94%20like%20between%20their%20paw%20pads%20or%20inside%20skin%20folds%20%E2%80%94%20can%20trigger%20skin%20irritation%20and%20infections.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20long-haired%20breeds%2C%20debris%20buildup%20can%20also%20cause%20matted%20fur%2C%20which%20can%20look%20unattractive%20and%20cause%20your%20dog%20discomfort.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EHow%20to%20bathe%20your%20dog%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20washing%20your%20dog%2C%20Wigfall%20says%20it's%20important%20to%20avoid%20getting%20any%20shampoo%20into%20their%20eyes%20or%20ears.%20Here%20are%20two%20things%20that%20can%20help%20with%20that%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EGently%20placing%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.akc.org%2Fexpert-advice%2Fhealth%2Fits-bath-time-towels-brushes-dog-shampoo-and-more%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecotton%20balls%20in%20their%20ears%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.akc.org%2Fexpert-advice%2Fhealth%2Fits-bath-time-towels-brushes-dog-shampoo-and-more%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApplying%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20mineral%20oil%20ointment%20in%20their%20eyes%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20Gently%20pull%20down%20the%20