ve%20phrases%2C%20and%20rewards%20whenever%20possible.%20Simon%20suggests%20keeping%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdevice-gets-your-dog-excited-for-bath-time-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elick%20mat%20smeared%20with%20peanut%20butter%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20another%20treat%20at%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20bath%20to%20keep%20them%20happy%20and%20distracted.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ERinse%20and%20repeat%20as%20needed%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EUsing%20your%20shower's%20handheld%20spray%20attachment%20can%20make%20rinsing%20your%20dog's%20coat%20much%20easier%2C%20Wigfall%20says.%20You%20can%20also%20use%20a%20pitcher%20or%20bucket%20to%20gently%20pour%20water%20on%20your%20dog%20to%20get%20the%20shampoo%20out.%20Make%20sure%20you've%20eliminated%20all%20traces%20of%20shampoo%20%E2%80%94%20this%20may%20take%20a%20handful%20of%20rinses.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EDry%20your%20dog%20thoroughly%20with%20a%20towel%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDry%20your%20dog%20thoroughly%20with%20a%20towel.%20Moisture%20and%20irritation%20on%20the%20skin%20create%20a%20breeding%20ground%20for%20bacteria%2C%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.akc.org%2Fexpert-advice%2Fhealth%2Ftreating-and-preventing-hot-spots-on-dogs%2F%5C%22%3Eacute%20moist%20dermatitis%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ETry%20a%20blow%20dryer%20if%20necessary.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIf%20towel%20drying%20doesn't%20do%20the%20job%2C%20which%20is%20often%20the%20case%20for%20dogs%20with%20longer%20hair%20or%20double%20coats%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-hair-dryer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblow%20dryer%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20help.%20Set%20it%20to%20the%20lowest%20heat%20setting%2C%20keep%20it%20a%20few%20inches%20away%20from%20your%20dog's%20coat%2C%20and%20continually%20move%20it%20in%20a%20back-and-forth%20motion.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWigfall%20suggests%20placing%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiauto-55886-20%26h%3Dcaba2faee2570b7d9d5014a05dff3fc48dca08ca30b1414ca61eea8a01f8b554%26postID%3D62fbf46cdda1a57dec5c15a9%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fpets%252Fhow-often-should-you-bathe-your-dog%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252Fdp%252FB07HZ4PQ96%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrippy%20mat%3C%2Fa%3E%20underneath%20your%20dog%20to%20keep%20them%20from%20slipping%20and%20sliding%20while%20you're%20bathing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EInsider's%20takeaway%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBathing%20your%20dog%20too%20often%20can%20lead%20to%20skin%20irritation%20and%20a%20dull%20coat%2C%20while%20not%20bathing%20them%20often%20enough%20could%20increase%20their%20risk%20of%20infections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20general%20rule%2C%20aim%20to%20bathe%20your%20dog%20every%20one%20to%20three%20months%20%E2%80%94%20erring%20on%20the%20more%20frequent%20side%20if%20they're%20hairless%2C%20have%20a%20long%20coat%2C%20or%20spend%20their%20days%20playing%20or%20working%20outdoors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20also%20keep%20their%20coat%20clean%20by%20brushing%20them%20often%20and%20rinsing%20them%20with%20plain%20water%20between%20baths.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20ever%20uncertain%20about%20how%20often%20to%20bathe%20your%20dog%2C%20you%20can%20always%20ask%20your%20vet%20for%20breed-specific%20guidance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3ECorrection%3A%20December%2030%2C%202022%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%E2%80%94%20An%20earlier%20version%20of%20this%20story%20quoted%20Amanda%20Takiguchi%2C%20a%20veterinarian%20who%20alerted%20us%20that%20a%20scammer%20had%20been%20impersonating%20her%20on%20a%20website%20that%20connects%20journalists%