l%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvetsource.com%2Fnews%2Fcommon-pet-health-problems%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20common%20%3C%2Fa%3Epet%20healthcare%20concerns%2C%20and%20it's%20crucial%20that%20as%20a%20pet%20parent%20you%20stay%20vigilant.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20to%20spot%20fleas%2C%20get%20rid%20of%20them%2C%20and%20prevent%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d6541550-f9a0-46da-b084-b2145124ad67%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20tell%20if%20your%20dog%20has%20fleas%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20dog%20has%20fleas%2C%20there%20will%20be%20a%20few%20telltale%20signs%20that%20your%20pup%20is%20getting%20bitten.%20Here's%20what%20you%20should%20do%20to%20check%20for%20fleas%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Notice%20if%20your%20dog%20is%20scratching%20more%20often%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20One%20of%20the%20tell-tale%20signs%20that%20your%20dog%20has%20fleas%20isn't%20the%20flea%20itself%2C%20it's%20your%20dog.%20If%20you%20notice%20your%20dog%20regularly%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.akc.org%2Fexpert-advice%2Fhealth%2Fflea-bites-on-dogs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escratching%2C%20biting%2C%20or%20chewing%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20their%20skin%20it%20could%20mean%20he's%20infected%20with%20fleas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Take%20a%20close%20look%20at%20your%20dog's%20fur%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Fleas%20are%20dark%20brown%20and%20very%20tiny%2C%20about%200.1%20to%200.3%20centimeters%20big%2C%20the%20size%20of%20a%20small%20crumb%2C%20but%20they're%20still%20able%20to%20be%20seen%20with%20the%20naked%20eye%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvetmedbiosci.colostate.edu%2Fdirectory%2Fmember%2F%3Fid%3D41390%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlison%20Meindl%2C%20DVM%2C%20DABVP%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvetmedbiosci.colostate.edu%2Fvth%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EColorado%20State%20University%20Veterinary%20Teaching%20Hospital%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20spot%20fleas%20by%20parting%20the%20hair%20of%20the%20dog%20and%20looking%20for%20them%20on%20their%20skin.%20If%20you%20find%20something%20that%20resembles%20a%20flea%20but%20you're%20not%20sure%2C%20a%20good%20indicator%20is%20that%20they%20will%20jump%2C%20not%20crawl%2C%20around.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlea%20combs%20have%20very%20tightly%20spaced%20teeth%2C%20which%20are%20designed%20to%20pull%20fleas%20away%20from%20the%20hair%20to%20better%20identify%20them.%20Your%20best%20bet%20for%20finding%20fleas%20on%20an%20infested%20dog%20is%20to%20comb%20the%20hair%20at%20the%20base%20of%20your%20dog's%20tail%2C%20Meindl%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Look%20for%20flea%20dirt%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20You%20can%20identify%20fleas%20by%20the%20presence%20of%20%26quot%3Bflea%20dirt%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-15110151674jg-20%26h%3Dfd2c8d4d9dc7827629d79f5f50ca60fee9c99d4ebd8f78e419ea53fb2fb22405%26postID%3D628f975ea2374776c7e87d27%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fpets%252Ffleas-on-dogs%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.rover.com%252Fblog%252Fthe-dog-people-panel%252Fdr-gary-richter%252F%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGary%20Richter%2C%20DVM%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20veterinary%20health%20expert%20with%20Rover.%20This%20%26quot%3Bdirt%26quot%3B%20is%20actually%20digested%20blood%2C%20and%20it%20looks%20like%20a%20dark%2C%20granular%20material%2C%20he%20says.%20If%20you%20put%20a%20little%20water%20on%20the%20substance%2C%20it%20will%20turn%20red.%20This%20is%20another%20surefire%20way%20to%20identify%20fleas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Check%20for%20bites%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EYou%20may%20also%20want%20to%20be%20on%20the%20lookout%20for%20flea%20bites%2C%20which%20look%20like%20small%20red%20bumps%20on%20your%20dog's%20skin%2C%20says%20Richter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224e502e0c-5e75-4d25-bb1d-7915d1ebea92%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20fleas%20on%20your%20dog%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20rid%20of%20your%20dog's%20fleas%2C%20Meindl%20says%20you%20can%20use%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-flea-treatment-dogs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evarious%20topical%20products%20or%20flea%20collars%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20will%20both%20kill%20and%20repel%20fleas.%20Oral%20medications%20are%20another%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20there%20anything%20to%20kill%20fleas%20on%20your%20dog%20instantly%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can't%20kill%20all%20the%20fleas%20on%20your%20dogs%20instantly%2C%20but%20you%20can%20kill%20them%20pretty%20quickly.%20%26quot%3BSome%20of%20the%20pharmaceutical%20products%20(usually%20the%20oral%20ones)%20will%20kill%20all%20of%20the%20fleas%20on%20the%20dog%20within%20an%20hour%20or%20two%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Richter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeindl%20says%20the%20most%20common%20ingredients%20in%20topical%20products%20and%20flea%20collars%20are%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMethoprene%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPyriproxyfen%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFipronil%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EImidacloprid%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPermethrins%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMethoprene%20and%20pyriproxyfen%20are%20growth%20regulators%2C%20which%20means%20they%20work%20by%20preventing%20juvenile%20fleas%20from%20molting%20into%20adults.%20Whereas%20fipronil%2C%20imidacloprid%2C%20and%20permethrin%20disrupt%20cellular%20function%2C%20which%20ultimately%20causes%20the%20fleas%20to%20die.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20of%20these%20drugs%20are%20very%20safe%20for%20both%20humans%20and%20dogs%20since%20they%20specifically%20target%20neurotransmitters%20that%20are%20more%20sensitive%20in%20insects%20as%20compared%20to%20mammals%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Meindl.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImportant%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Permethrin-containing%20products%20can%20be%20deadly%20to%20cats%2C%20so%20take%20extra%20caution%20if%20you%20have%20felines%20in%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeindl%20says%20most%20oral%20drugs%20fall%20under%20the%20class%20of%20isoxazolines.%20These%20drugs%20work%20by%20causing%20uncontrolled%20neuromuscular%20activity%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20death%20of%20the%20fleas.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2294049cc5-23ab-4402-b4bd-8ac1a30104c4%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20rid%20your%20home%20of%20fleas%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20will%20also%20need%20to%20clear%20your%20home%20of%20fleas.%20%26quot%3BIf%20fleas%20are%20found%20on%20a%20dog%20or%20cat%2C%20every%20animal%20in%20the%20household%20needs%20to%20be%20treated%20for%20fleas%20and%20placed%20on%20a%20flea%20preventive%2C%20and%20the%20environment%20must%20be%20cleaned%20well.%20If%20the%20environment%20and%20all%20animals%20are%20not%20treated%2C%20the%20flea%20problem%20will%20continue%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Meindl.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20clean%20the%20environment%2C%20Meindl%20says%20you%20should%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-vacuum%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVacuum%20all%20flooring%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20under%20furniture%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWash%20all%20bedding%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDispose%20of%20loose%20brush%20or%20overgrown%20vegetation%20in%20the%20yard%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHave%20the%20home%20and%20yard%20treated%20by%20a%20professional%20pest%20control%20company%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b6f80bd5-88b9-4e14-9502-4456cc016111%5C%22%3EPreventing%20fleas%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%20today%20we%20have%20more%20preventative%20medications%20to%20ward%20off%20fleas%20than%20ever%20before%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vetmed.auburn.edu%2Ffaculty%2Flea-christopher%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChristopher%20Lea%2C%20DVM%2C%20DABVP%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20clinician%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vetmed.auburn.edu%2Fanimal-owners%2Fau-veterinary-clinic%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAuburn%20University%20Veterinary%20Clinic%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20associate%20professor%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.auburn.edu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAuburn%20University%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20says%20the%20newer%20isoxazoline%20class%20of%20oral%20medications%20is%20%26quot%3Bunbelievably%20effective%26quot%3B%20at%20preventing%20fleas%20and%20ticks.%20Additionally%2C%20these%20drugs%20are%20very%20safe%20for%20dogs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20examples%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Fanimal-veterinary%2Fanimal-health-literacy%2Ffact-sheet-pet-owners-and-veterinarians-about-potential-adverse-events-associated-isoxazoline-flea%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrand%20names%20for%20the%20isoxazoline%20class%20%3C%2Fa%3Einclude%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-15110151674jg-20%26h%3D4b45e396299f8fff71fa70793a198669ddbec558b252f13673c983b26ae14b9d%26postID%3D628f975ea2374776c7e87d27%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fpets%252Ffleas-on-dogs%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.chewy.com%252Fbravecto-topical-solution-dogs-22-44%252Fdp%252F172897%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBravecto%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-15110151674jg-20%26h%3D58e